<item>
            <title>[HBASE-13221] HDFS Transparent Encryption breaks WAL writing in Hadoop 2.6.0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13221</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We need to detect when HDFS Transparent Encryption (Hadoop 2.6.0+) is enabled and fall back to more synchronization in the WAL to prevent catastrophic failure under load.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-11708&quot; title=&quot;CryptoOutputStream synchronization differences from DFSOutputStream break HBase&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-11708&quot;&gt;HADOOP-11708&lt;/a&gt; for more details.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12781520">HBASE-13221</key>
            <summary>HDFS Transparent Encryption breaks WAL writing in Hadoop 2.6.0</summary>
