                                    <watches>12</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14358827" author="busbey" created="Thu, 12 Mar 2015 15:34:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Additionally, when this was falling over it pointed out that the exception catching in AsyncWriter / AsyncSyncer needs to be more robust. We got IndexOutOfBoundsException and InternalError (!!), both of which caused the Writer / Syncer thread to exit. This deadlocked the RS since nothing could ever notify that WAL writes had completed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14358940" author="busbey" created="Thu, 12 Mar 2015 16:40:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This also impacts 0.94, because it does sync outside of the lock it uses to control appending entries. Anyone opposed to it just being a documentation change for 0.94 that says it won&apos;t work with the feature?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14516413" author="ndimiduk" created="Tue, 28 Apr 2015 05:37:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How&apos;s patch coming &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=busbey&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;busbey&quot;&gt;Sean Busbey&lt;/a&gt;? Do we have a Plan B for 1.1.0? How about detect when HDFS Transparent Encryption enabled and abort?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14517137" author="busbey" created="Tue, 28 Apr 2015 14:54:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a solution locally from back in mid-march, been waiting to get the time to do some perf comparisons so we can decide if it&apos;s better to just detect and abort or have a general solution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let me check on what the patch looks like now and get it posted up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14517300" author="ndimiduk" created="Tue, 28 Apr 2015 16:09:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We&apos;re down to the wire on 1.1. Let&apos;s either get a fix in or at least grind down the sharp edge.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14716941" author="busbey" created="Thu, 27 Aug 2015 16:06:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;what do folks think about repurposing this to just mark Hadoop 2.6.x as unsupported with a footnote explaining this issue? Once 2.6.1 exists we could update it say 2.6.1+ is fine?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14717012" author="stack" created="Thu, 27 Aug 2015 16:37:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=busbey&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;busbey&quot;&gt;Sean Busbey&lt;/a&gt; Sounds reasonable.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14720681" author="apurtell" created="Fri, 28 Aug 2015 22:16:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 for marking 2.6.0 as bad in doc &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14724767" author="busbey" created="Tue, 1 Sep 2015 04:17:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;-01&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Toggles Hadoop 2.6.x from S to X&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Adds tip with pointer for needed patch to run HBase on HDFS Encryption in 2.6 line.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14724901" author="hadoopqa" created="Tue, 1 Sep 2015 07:20:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;red&quot;&gt;-1 overall&lt;/font&gt;.  Here are the results of testing the latest attachment &lt;br/&gt;
